=99s cash flow from operations was $126 million, and its stock-based compen=
sation expense was $177 million. If it had to pay all of that compensation =
in cash, its cash flow would be negative, which does not leave a lot of mon=
ey to service the debt. I guess getting rid of some=C2=A0employees would he=
lp with this.That said, I have  also pointed out that the loans to Twitter =
and Musk aren=E2=80=99t that risky, because he is very rich and will not wa=
nt to lose his $21 billion or more of equity in Twitter by defaulting on th=
e loans. Here is a Financial Times story quoting his bankers saying similar=
 things:The [Tesla]=C2=A0share price will be closely watched by Musk=E2=80=
=99s lenders since it is their collateral should he default on his loan. Ba=
nkers said that security gave them confidence that Musk and Twitter would b=
