=A6=C2=A0what consequences? (The penalties for this stuff are small, and=C2=
=A0it=E2=80=99s not like they will prevent him from buying Twitter.) What=
=E2=80=99s the point? It will just be an exhausting slog of litigation and =
mean tweets and he will emerge unchastened and richer than ever, and then h=
e will try to stop the SEC lawyers from ever getting jobs in the private se=
ctor. Why should they bother? What is the point of trying to enforce the la=
