earnings release would say, because he declined to do any nonpublic due dil=
igence on Twitter, for reasons of speed and weirdness.[5]</li>=09<li style=
=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">If the earnings were great, and the board knew tha=
t, it would not have accepted $54.20 per share. It would have told its bank=
ers about its great earnings, and its prospects for great future earnings, =
and they would have built a model showing that Twitter was worth much more =
