ent. I did not have a great answer! Some readers had some suggestions, thou=
gh, which I=E2=80=99d like to discuss.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The =
basic story of Archegos is that it borrowed money to buy tons of shares of =
about 10 stocks, the stocks went up because it was buying them, it used its=
 profits to borrow more money to buy more shares, the stocks kept going up,=
 etc., until Archegos owned like half of the float of many of these stocks =
at inflated prices. And then something went slightly wrong, Archegos got ma=
rgin calls that it couldn=E2=80=99t meet because every penny was tied up in=
 these inflated stocks, its brokers dumped the stocks, the prices collapsed=
, there were more margin calls and more liquidations, and eventually Archeg=
os=E2=80=99s portfolio went to zero and its banks lost billions of dollars.=
</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;"><em>Why would he=C2=A0do this?=C2=A0</em>T=
he theory of the Department of Justice and the Securities and Exchange Comm=
ission is that Hwang was doing market manipulation, that he bought as much =
as he could of these stocks to make them go up. This theory might well be t=
rue, but it is very annoying, because this is not a way to make money. It i=
s a way to have large paper gains, sure, but in the SEC=E2=80=99s and DOJ=
=E2=80=99s telling he plowed every cent of those gains back into pushing th=
e stocks up more, which can only end the way it did. Bill Hwang is a smart =
guy and an experienced hedge fund manager. Perhaps he concocted a scheme to=
 put as much money as possible onto a pile and incinerate it all, but that =
is a dumb scheme.</p><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">My alternative theory was=
=C2=A0that Hwang could extracted some of his billions of dollar in profits =
=E2=80=94 by calling=C2=A0the banks up and saying =E2=80=9Chey I see I have=
 some profits in this account, could you wire them to me?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0and then buried them in his backyard.=C2=A0<em>Archegos=C2=A0</em>=
went to zero, but if Hwang extracted some money from Archegos and put it be=
yond the reach of margin calls=C2=A0<em>before=C2=A0</em>it went to zero, t=
hen he could be doing pretty well. (Except for being arrested.)</p><p style=
=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I said yesterday that this theory =E2=80=9Cseems ruled=
